kModal_main_2531871\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Aug 14, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104sad1665702964041.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/sad1665702964041.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/sad1665702964041.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"sad1665702964041\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n                       \n Sybase Performance Considerations \n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"sad1665702964041__sybase_performance_considerations_172955\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">You can use Sybase stored procedures and user options to improve the performance of your application.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"sad1665702964041__p_d59072e1_d59073e1_d59074e1\">Uniface implements the following features to improve performance:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"sad1665702964041__li_d26483e1_d26484e1_d26485e1\">Fields that are not in the component structure and are not explicitly mentioned in ProcScript, are not selected, fetched, inserted, or updated by the DBMS connector.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"sad1665702964041__li_d26486e1_d26487e1_d26488e1\">Sybase does not allow NULL bit fields. Therefore, the SYB connector converts any request to store a NULL bit field to store a 0 (FALSE), so the field is skipped.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"sad1665702964041__li_d26489e1_d26490e1_d26491e1\">The connector supports the Uniface stepped hitlist\n                                mechanism with a default step size of 10 by using Sybase cursors.\n                                        <div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"sad1665702964041__note_w3783ab1b5b5b5b1_w3784ab1b5b5b5_w3785ab1b5b5_w3786ab1b5_w3787ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> Sybase cursors may result in poor\n                                        performance if multiple sessions have to manage multiple\n                                        cursors. An alternative is to use the <code class=\"ph codeph\">same\n                                                select</code> option to disable the use of cursors\n                                        for hit list management. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"vbk1665702665020.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/vbk1665702665020.html#vbk1665702665020__section_nn4_ztv_jcc\">Same-Select Mechanism for Hitlist Management</a>.\n                                </div>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"sad1665702964041__li_d26492e1_d26493e1_d26494e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"sad1665702964041__p_d59075e1_d59076e1_d59077e1\">The SYB connector can work with a database that has been configured for chained transactions. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"nec1665702706915.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/nec1665702706915.html\" title=\"Both commit and rollback instruction are fully supported by Sybase.\">Transaction Control on Sybase</a>.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"sad1665702964041__p_d59078e1_d59079e1_d59080e1\">In addition, you can make use of the following options to influence the performance of your application:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"sad1665702964041__li_d26495e1_d26496e1_d26497e1\">To limit the number of returned hits, you can use <code class=\"ph codeph\">maxhits</code> parameter with the ProcScript <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">read</span> statement. You can also configure the step size using the <code class=\"ph codeph\">step</code> parameter.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"sad1665702964041__li_d26498e1_d26499e1_d26500e1\">Use Sybase stored procedures. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"xfd1665702778269.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/xfd1665702778269.html\" title=\"The SYB connector supports the use of Sybase stored procedures. These can also be activated as service stored procedures.\">Sybase Stored Procedures</a>.\n                        </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"sad1665702964041__li_d26501e1_d26502e1_d26503e1\">Use the <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"bft1665702734828.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/bft1665702734828.html\" title=\"Disable the Sybase connector check for stored procedures.\">disable proc check</a> option, if possible.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"sad1665702964041__li_d26504e1_d26505e1_d26506e1\">Use the <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"exm1665702661663.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/exm1665702661663.html\" title=\"Set the number of rows the connector selects from the DBMS in each step of the Uniface stepped hitlist.\">step size</a> option to configure the size of each step in the hitlist.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"sad1665702964041__li_d26507e1_d26508e1_d26509e1\">Use the <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"kly1665702735187.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kly1665702735187.html\" title=\"Set the Sybase packet size.\">tds_packetsize</a> option to control the size of data packets\n </li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2531871\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2531871\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Sybase Performance Considerations Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Aug 14, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Sybase Performance Considerations You can use Sybase stored procedures and user options to improve the performance of your application. Uniface implements the following features to improve performance: Fields that are not in the component structure and are not explicitly mentioned in ProcScript, are not selected, fetched, inserted, or updated by the DBMS connector. Sybase does not allow NULL bit fields. Therefore, the SYB connector converts any request to store a NULL bit field to store a 0 (FALSE), so the field is skipped. The connector supports the Uniface stepped hitlist mechanism with a default step size of 10 by using Sybase cursors. Note: Sybase cursors may result in poor performance if multiple sessions have to manage multiple cursors. An alternative is to use the same select option to disable the use of cursors for hit list management. For more information, see Same-Select Mechanism for Hitlist Management . The SYB connector can work with a database that has been configured for chained transactions. For more information, see Transaction Control on Sybase . In addition, you can make use of the following options to influence the performance of your application: To limit the number of returned hits, you can use maxhits parameter with the ProcScript read statement. You can also configure the step size using the step parameter. Use Sybase stored procedures. For more information, see Sybase Stored Procedures . Use the disable proc check option, if possible. Use the step size option to configure the size of each step in the hitlist. Use the tds_packetsize option to control the size of data packets Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}